{"word":"surement","priority":"★★☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"adverb","definition":"確かに、きっと、必ず","english_definition":"certainly; surely; undoubtedly","examples":[{"sentence":"Il viendra surement demain.","translation":"彼はきっと明日来るでしょう。"},{"sentence":"C'est surement la meilleure solution.","translation":"それは確かに最良の解決策です。"}],"collocations":["surement pas (決して～ない)","surement que (きっと～だろう)","plus que surement (ほぼ確実に)"],"synonyms":["certainement","indubitablement","sans doute","à coup sûr"],"antonyms":["peut-être","probablement pas"]}],"etymology":{"value":"古フランス語の「seür」(安全な、確かな)に由来し、ラテン語の「securus」(安全な、心配のない)から派生。接尾辞「-ment」が付加され副詞化。","priority":"★☆☆"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/syʁ.mɑ̃/","syllables":"su-re-ment"},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「surement」は確信や強い可能性を表す副詞で、文頭・文中・文尾のいずれにも置けます。否定形「surement pas」で「決して～ない」の意味になります。会話では「sûr」と短縮されることもあります。","priority":"★★☆"},"common_mistakes":{"examples":[{"incorrect":"✗ Je ne sais surement pas","correct":"✓ Je ne sais certainement pas","note":"「surement pas」は未来の否定推量に使うのが自然。現在の事実には「certainement pas」が適切"}],"priority":"★☆☆"},"related_words":{"derivatives":["sûr (形容詞: 確かな)","sûreté (名詞: 確実性)"],"priority":"★☆☆"},"level_frequency":{"CEFR":"B1","frequency_google_ngram":"中頻度","priority":"★☆☆"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"Tu as surement raison.","translation":"君はきっと正しい。","type":"adverb","meaning_category":"確信"},{"sentence":"Il n'a surement pas compris.","translation":"彼はきっと理解していなかった。","type":"adverb (否定)","meaning_category":"強い否定推量"}]}